            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-25 13:33:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to not providing a reason or cause, in view of something being contrary to reason</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>unreasonable</Gloss>
                <Gloss>without basis</Gloss>
                <Gloss>absurd</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages the equivalent of being unreasonable is being something which people should not think. Note that ἄλογος[b] refers to that which is contrary to proper reasoning, while ἄλογος[a] ({D:30.12}) pertains to a lack of capacity to reason.</Comments>
